--- per-table forms (db.table and bare table) ---
SYSTEM STOP db.t
SYSTEM START db.t
SYSTEM PAUSE db.t
SYSTEM CANCEL db.t
SYSTEM REFRESH db.t
SYSTEM STOP t
SYSTEM START t
SYSTEM PAUSE t
SYSTEM CANCEL t
SYSTEM REFRESH t
--- ALL BACKGROUND forms ---
SYSTEM STOP ALL BACKGROUND
SYSTEM START ALL BACKGROUND
SYSTEM PAUSE ALL BACKGROUND
SYSTEM CANCEL ALL BACKGROUND
SYSTEM REFRESH ALL BACKGROUND
--- the bare verbs must not shadow the existing keyword forms ---
SYSTEM STOP MERGES db.t
SYSTEM START MERGES db.t
SYSTEM STOP VIEW db.v
SYSTEM START VIEW db.v
SYSTEM PAUSE VIEW db.v
SYSTEM CANCEL VIEW db.v
SYSTEM REFRESH VIEW db.v
SYSTEM STOP VIEWS
SYSTEM START VIEWS
SYSTEM PAUSE VIEWS
--- table names that collide with command keywords need backticks ---
SYSTEM STOP db.background
SYSTEM STOP `all`
--- ON CLUSTER is not supported (matches the SYSTEM ... VIEW aliases) ---
--- only tables with controllable background activity are accepted ---
